    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors not assessed are acceptable per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 requirements. CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating point; RH < 1 at all 5 COU operating conditions. Mean nIH error of 8.3% is within the 15% acceptance criterion. The experimental validation dataset (vintage 2025-10-01) predates the January 2026 model revision that updated boundary-layer mesh density and turbulence-model constants; re-validation against refreshed experimental data is planned for Q2 2026. The review board judges this gap acceptable given that hydraulic performance metrics are unchanged and the mesh update is expected to reduce, not increase, hemolysis prediction error. Decision: Accepted with recommendation to complete post-revision re-validation prior to next design iteration.",
